# Maestro — **every time** you touch this project

**On every change** to flows (`.yaml`/`.yml`), `config.yaml`, or scripts that invoke Maestro (`.bat`, `.ps1`, `.sh`), you MUST align with **[Maestro documentation](https://docs.maestro.dev/)**. Do not rely on memory alone — open the official pages below when editing.

Verify **every time** against:

- **[Maestro CLI commands and options](https://docs.maestro.dev/maestro-cli/maestro-cli-commands-and-options)** — global flags (`--device`, `--udid`), `maestro test` options (`--format`, `--output`, `--debug-output`, `--config`, etc.).
- **[Flows](https://docs.maestro.dev/)** — YAML structure, `config.yaml`, nested flows.

### CLI conventions (from official docs)

- Pattern: `maestro [global options] test [test options] <flow(s)>`
- Prefer **named parameters** in CI scripts (see docs: *Named parameters* section).
- Device: `--device <id>` or `--udid <id>` (global, **before** `test`). Tables on the docs site may show `--device=`; **this repo uses space-separated values** (`--device SERIAL`).
- `test` options: use **space-separated** values, e.g. `--format junit`, `--output report.xml`, `--debug-output path`, `--config config.yaml` (matches typical Maestro CLI usage; verify on the [CLI page](https://docs.maestro.dev/maestro-cli/maestro-cli-commands-and-options)).

Do **not** invent flags; if unsure, check the docs site above.
